{"editorCode":"  ;The avatar is a bit...drunk.\n;Everytime we run the procedure \"step\", the avatar goes either 10 units forward or 10 units backwards, randomly.\n;The way it goes is printed at the down area of the editor (where messages are printed).\n;The procedure \"path\" makes the avatar do n number of this kind of drunk movement.\n\n;What is the possibility for the avatar to reach the door step of its house? (the bottom horizontal red line of the house), that is only two \"steps\" away?\n\n;For further instructions click on the papyrus button.\n\n\nTO step\nmake \"random rand 2\nIf :random=0 [print 'backwards']\nIf :random=1 [print 'forward']\nfd 20*:random - 10\nrt 90 fd 2 bk 4 fd 2 lt 90\nend\n\nclean\nstep\n\n\nto walk :n\nsetpencolor [255 0 0 ] ;red\nrt 90 fd 20 bk 40 fd 20 lt 90\nsetpencolor [0 0 0] ;black\nrepeat :n [step]\nprint '-----------'\nend\n\nclean\nwalk 5\n\n\nTO house\npu home fd 20 pd\nsetpencolor [255 0 0 ] ;red\nlt 90 fd 20\nrt 90 fd 40 \nrt 30 fd 40\nrepeat 2 [rt 120 fd 40] bk 40 \nlt 90 fd 40\nrt 90 fd 20 \nrt 90\nsetpencolor [0 0 0] ;black \npu home pd\nend\n\nclean \nhouse\nwalk 4\n\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"       The random steps\n                                                 ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n\nTASK 1\n----------------------------\nRun the command \"walk 10\". Count how many times did the avatar go forward and backwards from the messages at the bottom area of the editor.\n\nCan this help you understand if, when the avatar makes a drunk step, the possibility for it to go forward is the same as the one for it to go backwards?\n\n\nTASK 2\n----------------------------\nAfter \"erasing\" the messages from the editor, run the following commands:\n\nclean\nhouse\nwalk 4\n\nBy running these commands, you make an \"random experiment\", where the avatar, beginning from its starting point, makes 4 drunk steps. You can repeat the experiment as many times as you want.\nThis will help you answer the following questions: \n\na) Use a tree diagram in order to find all the possible results of this experiment. \nWhat is the possibility for the avatar to reach (with its belly) the exact point on the door step of the house (the red horizontal line) which is only two (forward) steps away?\n    \nb) If the door step was 4 (forward) steps away, do you believe that the possibility for the avatar to reach it would be higher or lower than the possibility when it is 2 steps away?\n\n\n\n\n\n\n ","sliders":{},"objects":[]}